"HC = \"already corrected by 3 star heights and red-orange Betelgeuse color\". Corrections have been applied, -0.00mag due to different zenith distances of Pollux(33°), Betelgeuse(43°), Bellatrix(46°), and +0.04mag due to their different colors. The magnitude attenuation for a star with a zenith distance z and for the local sky is roughly   k/cos(z)   with k=0.20 in V band, k=0.17 for Betelgeuse (see Christian Buil, http://www.astrosurf.com/aras/extinction/calcul.htm)."
